u5UtrJC0eNSWnnc9nYhzchysNk6jAYa7ZqNmIeBKcWdcGOOjmKx0-U=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Android API accessibility**\\n\\nI’m considering the Android API's accessibility through a helper fake android API and how `Class.forName` behaves. It seems I need to ensure that the class is initialized to work properly, and that native images recognize classes properly. I have some uncertainty about method accessibility, especially since it affects coverage for Android-specific code in the JVM. It might be better to ensure that the test class loader loads the Memory class before calling any methods from UnsafeUtil.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preparing for code adjustments**\\n\\nI need to check if the `CodedOutputStream` class should be statically initialized before the fake Memory, since importing doesn't load it automatically. There might also be an issue with the generated Scala package blocks due to a file name path mismatch. I think all top-level test classes should be public, including Memory. I should clarify if my style needs to align with Scala 2 or 3, and it looks like my build is on Scala 3. JUnit has the necessary API, so I should commit the changes after confirming the status.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_AYfhHwJx28RJpBHlMt7zwEnU|fc_061844c4710a40310169f387cedaf0819091b5cfa893a3df40", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git status --short && git diff -- tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/src/test/scala/org_apache_pekko/pekko_protobuf_v3_3/UnsafeUtilTest.scala", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 724, "output": 880, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40004, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777567676819, "responseId": "resp_061844c4710a40310169f387be0b9c8190bcf619ba2d9db18a"}}
